-- FACTBOX-Loan loss provisions of big euro zone banks in 2013 
-- 
-- Tue Apr 15, 2014 01:00AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 15 (Reuters) - The euro zone's 20 largest quoted banks took a combined 71.5 billion euros of loan loss provisions in 2013. [ID:nL6N0MZ0YQ]

The breakdown of how much was booked by each bank is below:EUR mln  Unicredit<CRDI.MI>  13,658  Santander<SAN.MC>   10,863  Intesa Sanpaolo<ISP.MI>  7,131  BBVA<BBVA.MC>5,776  CaixaBank<CABK.MC>   4,329  BNP Paribas<BNPP.PA> 4,054  Societe Generale<SOGN.PA>4,052  Credit Agricole<CAGR.PA> 2,961  Banco Popular Espanol<POP.MC>2,324  ING<ING.AS>  2,288  Deutsche Bank<DBKGn.DE>  2,029  Sabadell<SABE.MC>1,764  Erste Bank<ERST.VI>  1,763  Commerzbank<CBKG.DE> 1,747  KBC<KBC.BR>  1,719  Bank of Ireland<BKIR.I>  1,665  Bankia<BKIA.MC>  1,249  Raiffeisen<RBIV.VI>  1,149  Mediobanca<MDBI.MI>576  Natixis<CNAT.PA>   392  Total   71,489